  "text": "Wolff et al. [CITATION_1] present a distributed data mining approach based on a decentralized algorithm to test whether the Euclidean norm of the average of vectors is within a threshold. They apply a leaky bucket algorithm for rate limiting, which makes their system periodic (thus, proactive). Here, a significant improvement in convergence speed could be expected using simple token bucket algorithms instead, and further optimization using our various token account algorithms may be possible.",
